The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a vector or matrix from quadratic measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and computer vision. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), or cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses connections to low-rank matrix recovery and nonsingular bilinear forms, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
